Pavel Machek <pavel@suse.cz> wrote:
> xargs is very ugly. I want to rm 12*. Just plain "rm 12*". *Not* "find
> . -name "12*" | xargs rm, which has terrible issues with files names
Try
printf "%s\0" 12* | xargs -0 rm
